http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/%E2%80%98Free-diagnostic-tests-at-govt.-hospitals-from-Feb.-1%E2%80%99/article13986148.ece

Chief Minister N. Chandrababu Naidu on Wednesday said all government hospitals in the State would be developed on the lines of corporate hospitals. Speaking after inaugurating the maternity and children’s block at the district hospital at Nandyal, he said all diagnostic tests at government hospitals would be done free of cost from February 1 under the NTR Vaidya Seva scheme. He added that each family was entitled to free medicare up to Rs. 2.50 lakh.Mr. Naidu said the maintenance of government hospitals would be entrusted to DWCRA groups.The Chief Minister also launched the ‘Thalli Bidda Express’ scheme to take care of mother and child and provide them transport from government hospitals to their houses after institutional delivery.